  A `rule @never audit` whose attribute has no carriers anywhere: the rule runs
  vacuously and the program compiles and runs clean — a zero-carrier attribute
  anchor is not an error (a typo'd attribute cannot be diagnosed in Phase 2a).
-#

rule @never audit

fn main(u32 argc, u8 **argv) -> i32 {
    return 7
}
